  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What is N1QL?', '["SQL-like querying over JSON documents","A backup tool","A replication protocol","An index type"]'::jsonb, 0, 'N1QL/SQL++ lets you query JSON with familiar SQL syntax.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'How do buckets relate to scopes and collections?', '["Buckets are top-level; scopes/collections organize documents within","Collections contain buckets","They are the same thing","Scopes contain buckets"]'::jsonb, 0, 'A bucket holds scopes, which hold collections of documents.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What index type backs N1QL queries?', '["GSI (Global Secondary Index)","B-tree heap","GIN","Bitmap"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Global Secondary Indexes power efficient N1QL queries.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What is XDCR?', '["Cross-datacenter replication","An index format","A query cache","A backup CLI"]'::jsonb, 0, 'XDCR replicates data across clusters/regions.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What does the memory-first architecture give you?', '["Low-latency reads and writes","Strong relational joins","Automatic SQL migrations","Smaller disk usage"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Serving from memory first yields fast access with async persistence.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'How does Couchbase combine cache and database?', '["An integrated managed cache sits in front of persistence","It calls out to Redis","It uses the OS page cache only","It has no cache"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The built-in cache and storage are one system, avoiding a separate cache tier.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does Multi-Dimensional Scaling (MDS) allow?', '["Scaling data, query, and index services independently","Only vertical scaling","Sharding by hash slot","Replacing N1QL"]'::jsonb, 0, 'MDS lets you scale each service to its own workload/bottleneck.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does XDCR provide for resilience?', '["Multi-region replication for DR and locality","Stronger single-node consistency","Automatic indexing","Query caching"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Replicating across datacenters supports disaster recovery and low-latency access.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What durability options does Couchbase offer on write?', '["Configurable persistence and replication acknowledgement","None — writes are fire-and-forget","Only full-cluster sync","Only single-node"]'::jsonb, 0, 'You can require writes to persist/replicate to N nodes before acknowledging.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does a GSI enable for queries?', '["Efficient N1QL queries that scale independently of data nodes","Faster backups","Stronger consistency","Smaller documents"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Global Secondary Indexes can be hosted on dedicated index nodes.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What advantage does memory-first give over a separate cache + DB?', '["No separate cache-invalidation layer to keep consistent","It needs more services","It removes durability","It forbids querying"]'::jsonb, 0, 'One integrated store avoids the consistency headaches of a bolt-on cache.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'How does MDS help with bottlenecks?', '["Scale the specific service (query/index/data) that is constrained","Scale everything equally only","Disable services","Add more buckets"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Independent scaling targets the actual bottleneck without overprovisioning the rest.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What is the tradeoff of eventually consistent GSIs?', '["Fast queries versus possible slight index staleness","Always stale data","No querying","Slower writes only"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Indexes update asynchronously, so a query may briefly miss the newest write (tunable with scan consistency).'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'How does XDCR handle concurrent conflicting updates?', '["Via conflict resolution (e.g. revision/sequence-based)","It drops both writes","It blocks all writes","It cannot replicate writes"]'::jsonb, 0, 'XDCR resolves conflicts deterministically using revision metadata.'),
  ('Couchbase', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'Why choose Couchbase over a cache + RDBMS combo?', '["A unified low-latency store reduces operational complexity","It is always cheaper","It supports SQL joins better than any RDBMS","It needs no indexes"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Combining cache and database removes a moving part and its consistency burden.'),
  ('Redis', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'What is Redis?', '["An in-memory key-value data store","A relational database","A document database","A message broker only"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Redis keeps data in memory for very fast access.'),
  ('Redis', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'Why is Redis fast?', '["Data lives in RAM","It uses many disks","It compresses everything","It runs on the GPU"]'::jsonb, 0, 'In-memory storage avoids disk latency.'),
