  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'Where is a SQLite database stored?', '["In a single file","On a dedicated server","In RAM only","Across many nodes"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The whole database is a single cross-platform file.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'Does SQLite need a server process?', '["No — it runs in-process","Yes, always","Only for writes","Only on mobile"]'::jsonb, 0, 'SQLite is serverless and embedded in the application.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'What language queries SQLite?', '["SQL","N1QL","PromQL","GraphQL"]'::jsonb, 0, 'SQLite uses standard SQL.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'What is a common SQLite use case?', '["Mobile/embedded/local app storage","Massive multi-writer web backend","Distributed analytics","Real-time pub/sub"]'::jsonb, 0, 'SQLite excels for local, embedded, low-concurrency storage.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What concurrency model does SQLite use?', '["File-level locking with one writer at a time","Row-level locking","Lock-free MVCC","No locking"]'::jsonb, 0, 'SQLite serializes writers; multiple readers are allowed.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What does WAL mode improve?', '["Concurrent readers alongside a writer","Multi-writer throughput","Network access","Encryption"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Write-Ahead Logging lets readers proceed while a write is in progress.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'Is SQLite suited to high write concurrency?', '["No — a single writer limits it","Yes, unlimited writers","Only with sharding","Only in WAL mode for writers"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Its single-writer model isn''t ideal for write-heavy concurrent servers.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What typing model does SQLite use?', '["Dynamic typing with type affinity","Strict static typing always","No types","Only text"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Columns have affinities but values can be of varying types.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What is a benefit of being serverless?', '["Zero-config, in-process, portable single file","Built-in replication","Multi-writer scaling","Automatic sharding"]'::jsonb, 0, 'No setup or server makes SQLite trivial to embed and ship.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does WAL mode change about reads and writes?', '["Readers don''t block the writer and vice versa","It allows many writers","It disables transactions","It removes durability"]'::jsonb, 0, 'WAL separates writes into a log so reads see a consistent snapshot concurrently.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'Why isn''t SQLite ideal for high-concurrency servers?', '["The single-writer lock serializes writes","It lacks SQL support","It can''t store text","It needs a server"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Concurrent writes queue behind one writer, limiting throughput.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What is type affinity?', '["Columns suggest a preferred type but don''t strictly enforce it","Strict type checking","An index type","A locking mode"]'::jsonb, 0, 'SQLite stores values with flexible types guided by column affinity.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'When is SQLite a great fit?', '["Local-first, embedded, read-heavy, low-concurrency apps","High-write multi-tenant SaaS","Distributed analytics clusters","Global pub/sub"]'::jsonb, 0, 'It shines for on-device and embedded scenarios.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does PRAGMA journal_mode control?', '["Rollback journal vs WAL behavior","Encryption keys","User permissions","Index types"]'::jsonb, 0, 'journal_mode switches between the default rollback journal and WAL.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'Why can SQLite outperform a client-server DB for local workloads?', '["No network/IPC — direct in-process file access","It uses more threads","It caches on the GPU","It skips SQL parsing"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Eliminating client-server round trips makes local access very fast.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What is the write-concurrency ceiling and its mitigation?', '["One writer; batch in transactions and use WAL","Unlimited writers; no mitigation needed","Zero writers; read-only","Two writers; add a server"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Group writes into transactions and enable WAL to maximize throughput within the single-writer limit.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What is the durability tradeoff of PRAGMA synchronous=OFF?', '["Faster writes but risk of corruption on power loss","Slower but safer writes","No effect","Stronger durability"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Skipping fsyncs speeds writes but can corrupt the file if the OS/host crashes.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'Why is SQLite among the most deployed databases in the world?', '["It''s embedded in countless apps, browsers, phones, and OSes","It runs the biggest web servers","It''s the fastest analytics engine","It requires a license per device"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Being a tiny, dependency-free embedded library, it ships inside billions of devices.'),
  ('SQLite', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'How does dynamic typing differ from strict SQL types?', '["Values retain their own type largely regardless of column affinity","Types are enforced at insert","All values become text","Types can''t be mixed"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Unless STRICT tables are used, SQLite stores the value''s type, guided (not bound) by affinity.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'What is HubSpot?', '["A CRM and marketing/sales platform","A relational database","A container runtime","A bundler"]'::jsonb, 0, 'HubSpot is a CRM with marketing, sales, and service tools.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'easy', 'What does CRM stand for?', '["Customer Relationship Management","Customer Resource Module","Central Record Manager","Cloud Resource Monitor"]'::jsonb, 0, 'CRM = Customer Relationship Management.'),
