  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'What does the HubSpot API let you do?', '["Read/write CRM data programmatically","Render dashboards only","Manage servers","Compile code"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The API exposes CRM objects for integrations and automation.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'mid', 'How do static and active lists differ?', '["Static has fixed membership; active auto-updates by criteria","They are identical","Active is fixed; static updates","Both are manual"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Active lists re-evaluate membership automatically as records change.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What does a workflow automate based on enrollment?', '["Actions like emails, property updates, and tasks","Server scaling","Code deployment","Index creation"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Enrolled records trigger automated sequences of actions.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What is an association in HubSpot?', '["A relationship between objects (contact-company-deal)","A user permission","An email template","A report filter"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Associations link records across object types.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'Why use custom objects?', '["To model business-specific entities beyond standard objects","To speed up the API","To replace properties","To store backups"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Custom objects represent data unique to your business.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What do API rate limits require of integrations?', '["Throttling and batching requests","Disabling auth","Polling constantly","Ignoring errors"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Respecting limits means batching and backing off to avoid 429s.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'high', 'What is HubSpot''s data model centered on?', '["Objects, properties, and associations","Tables and foreign keys","Buckets and documents","Streams and topics"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The CRM is built around objects with properties and associations.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'Why design properties and associations carefully up front?', '["They shape reporting/automation and are costly to refactor later","They only affect colors","They have no long-term impact","They are read-only"]'::jsonb, 0, 'The data model underpins reports and workflows, so early mistakes are expensive.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What is the core challenge of two-way CRM sync?', '["Conflict resolution and avoiding update loops","Rendering dashboards","Compiling code","Indexing"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Bidirectional sync must reconcile conflicting edits and prevent echo loops.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'How do you respect API rate limits at scale?', '["Use batch endpoints, backoff, and webhooks instead of polling","Send more requests faster","Disable retries","Ignore 429s"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Batching and event-driven webhooks reduce request volume against limits.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'Why prefer webhooks over polling for CRM changes?', '["Near-real-time updates without wasting rate limit","They are easier to disable","They store more data","They avoid authentication"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Webhooks push changes as they happen, avoiding constant polling.'),
  ('HubSpot', 'Databases & CRM', 'ultra', 'What does CRM data hygiene (dedup/validation) prevent?', '["Skewed reporting and broken automation from dirty data","Faster APIs","Smaller storage only","Login failures"]'::jsonb, 0, 'Clean, deduplicated data keeps reports accurate and workflows reliable.'),
  ('React', 'Frontend & Mobile', 'easy', 'What does JSX let you write?', '["HTML-like markup inside JavaScript","Inline SQL queries","CSS-only templates","Compiled WebAssembly"]'::jsonb, 0, 'JSX is syntax sugar for React.createElement calls, letting you write markup in JS.'),
  ('React', 'Frontend & Mobile', 'easy', 'Which hook adds local state to a function component?', '["useState","useEffect","useRef","useContext"]'::jsonb, 0, 'useState returns the current state and a setter.'),
